               stealing, on the <rs id="t18180909-283-cd1566" type="crimeDate">12th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-283-off1565 t18180909-283-cd1566"></join>, one handkerchief, value 2s., the goods of a certain person unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180909-283-person2002">
                  SAMUEL 
                  LACK
               <interp inst="t18180909-283-person2002" type="surname" value="LACK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-283-person2002" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180909-283-person2002" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a smith, and live in Russell-street, Covent Garden. On the 12th of July, between twelve and one o'clock in the day, I saw the prisoner in company with another man following a gentleman through <placeName id="t18180909-283-crimeloc1567">Russell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-283-crimeloc1567" type="placeName" value="Russell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180909-283-crimeloc1567" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180909-283-off1565 t18180909-283-crimeloc1567"></join>. I was at my window, up two-pair of stairs; I saw Gower take the handkerchief from the gentleman's pocket and throw it to Bruce, who tucked it into his waistcoat. I ran down, went out, and found them with the other man in Drury-lane. I took the prisoners into custody; the other man got away. I found the handkerchief in Bruce's waistcoat; I found another in Bruce's hat, and two others in his pocket. Somebody on the opposite side called to them to resist.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. They were on the opposite side to me.</p>
               <p>GOWER'S Defence. The handkerchief is my father's.</p>
               <p>GOWER - <rs id="t18180909-283-verdict1568" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180909-283-verdict1568" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs> Aged 17.</p>
               <p>BRUCE - <rs id="t18180909-283-verdict1569" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180909-283-verdict1569" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 21.</p>
